{
  "stem": "7506.7",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had a cousin who lived in Johannesburg, South Africa, [PAUSES] a first cousin of my-- both my parents, because they were cousins to each other.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he came to England to see us, to see my mother, me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he tried to get us to go to South Africa.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother didn't want to leave her grandmother, her sister, and her sister [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Anne, ?] and her brothers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they decided not to go to South Africa.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that uncle from South Africa gave my mother some money.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES] And my mother's eldest brother found my mother an apartment where to live.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I then lived with my mother in the apartment, and my mother went to work-- as a milliner, again-- [PAUSES] while I was being apprenticed in the beauty business.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The law in England before World War II was that if a woman married a foreigner, she lost her nationality, according to British law.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Germans never knew that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But when my mother came back, and wanted to remain in England, she had to reapply for her British citizenship back.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And after the war, they changed the law, because so many English-born women had been caught in Europe.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they changed the law in England, whereby she could regain her British nationality.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And because I was under 18, I had the choice of either remaining Dutch national, or becoming British.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I chose to be British.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The unfortunate thing, which I didn't realize at the time, [PAUSES] that at that time, around about 1948, '49, Britain had conscription.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES] That meant, and would've meant, that I would have had to go into the military in England.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was no way I was going to be taught how to kill people.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
